----
promise -> is an object, three states : pending,fulfilled, rejected . methods=> .then() .catch()

async await -> await keyword available only inside the async, the await keywords pauses the async function until a promise is settled

closures -> A closure in JavaScript is a function's ability to remember and access its surrounding state (lexical environment) even after the outer function has finished executing.
            A closure is the combination of a function bundled together (enclosed) with references to its surrounding state (the lexical environment)
            In other words, a closure gives a function access to its outer scope. 
virtual dom -> virtual DOM is a lightweight copy of the real DOM that allows React to manage changes more efficiently by minimizing the direct manipulation required on the real DOM. 
              This process significantly enhances the performance of web

mongoose -> Mongoose is a library that simplifies interacting with MongoDB. 

mvc service handlers -> They act as intermediaries between the controllers and the models, handling complex operations, data transformations, and interactions with external resources.

static files -> Static files in JavaScript refer to files that are served to the user's browser exactly as they are stored on the server. 

